Homemade phool makhana curry!
•
•
PROCESS:
👉Take a kadai and add 1 cube butter and roast phool makhana’s till slight golden brown 
👉add pepper powder and salt while roasting 
👉Add 1c oil, 1tbs jeera seeds, 1 cinnamon sticks, 1-2 start anise, 5-6 cloves, 1tbs black cumin seeds, 4-5 green cardamom seeds, 1tbs fennel seeds, 1tbs poppy seeds, 1/2c sliced green chilies, 1c chopped onions, 1tbs salt, 1c almonds & cashews, 1c mint leaves, 1c chopped tomatoes, 4-5 garlic, 1 ginger piece 
👉fry for 5-10mins and set a side 
👉once it cools down grind into fine paste 
👉add 1/2 cube butter, 2tbs oil, 3-4 bay leaves, 7-8 curry leaves, 5-6 sliced green chilies, 1/2tbs turmeric powder, 1tbs red chili powder, 1tbs coriander powder, 1/2tbs garam masala
👉add the paste and cook for 5-10mins
👉add fried phool makhana, 1c coconut milk, 2tbs cream 
👉cook until it thickens 
👉add some chopped cilantro and serve hot with some paratha and rice

Red poha/ Red Chura recipe!
•
•
You can use regular poha instead of the red poha but just follow the same recipe🤤
•
•
PROCESS:
👉Take a pan add 2tbs olive oil, 1tbs mustard seeds, 1tbs cumin seeds, 1tbs urad Dal, 1tbs Chana dal, 1/4c peanuts, 4-5 chopped green chilies, 1/2c chopped onions, 5-6 curry leaves and fry for 5mins
👉Add 1/2c sweet corn, 1tbs salt, 1tbs ginger garlic paste, 1/2tbs turmeric powder, 1tbs coriander powder, 1tbs black pepper powder and cook for another 5mins
👉Soak red poha in water for 4-5mins and drain the water 
👉now add it to the mixture and give it a nice mix
👉cook for another 5-10mins and add some chopped coriander leaves
👉finally turn off the flame and serve hot with some lemon and chopped onions

Quick meal with brown rice!
•
•
PROCESS:
👉Take a bowl and add 2c brown rice, wash and soak it in 6c water 
👉After 5-10mins, cook the brown rice on medium flame and set a side
👉Take a pan and add 3tbs olive oil, 1/4c chopped green chilies, 1c chopped onions, 1/4c chopped garlic and fry for 5mins
👉Add 1c chopped green beans, 1tbs salt and let it cook till the beans become soft 
👉Add 1c boiled chickpeas, 2tbs black pepper powder, 1tbs red chili flakes, 1tbs soya sauce(optional), 2tbs grated coconut and cook for 5mins
👉Add cooked brown rice and give it a nice mix
👉let it cook for another 5mins and turn off the flame
👉serve hot with some chopped onions, lemon juice and curd

Hyderabadi style Egg biryani!
•
•
PROCESS:
For rice:
👉Take a bowl, add 2c basmati rice and soak it in some water 
👉Take a kadai and add 6-7 cups water, add 2-3 cinnamon sticks, 1 star anise, 4-5 cardamom seeds, 4-5 cloves, 1 marathi Moggu, 4-5 bay leaves, 1tbs cumin seeds, 1tbs black cumin seeds, 1tbs salt, 1tbs ginger garlic paste, 1c chopped cilantro and mint leaves
👉let it come to boil and add rice 10mins before the gravy gets ready 
👉cook the rice until 3/4th softness
•
For gravy:
👉Take a pan and add 2tbs oil, 2tbs ghee👉add 1/4c sliced green chilies, 1c chopped onions, 1tbs ginger garlic paste, 1tbs turmeric powder, 1tbs salt, 2tbs red chili powder, 1c chopped tomatoes, 2tbs yogurt/curd and let it cook for 5-10mins
👉add 1tbs coriander powder, 1tbs garam masala and 4 boiled eggs 
👉let it cook until the gravy thickens to half
👉separate half of the gravy with 2 eggs and set a side in a bowl
👉drain the water and add the 3/4th cooked rice on top of the gravy 
👉add another layer of gravy that is in the bowl and cover it up with rice
👉top with some chopped coriander leaves and fried onions
👉cover it up with silver foil and let it cook on low flame for 20-25mins 
👉finally serve hot with lemon and onions

Airfried Beetroot cutlet/ tikki !
•
•
PROCESS:
👉Take a pressure cooker and add 1c overnight soaked green Moong dal
👉Add 2c water and 1/2tbs salt 
👉cook for 1 whistle, drain the water and set a side
👉Take 1 beetroot, grate it, add 1/2tbs salt and set a side
👉Take a bowl and add cooked Moong dal, 1/2c chopped onions, 1/4c chopped chilies

Homemade Mutton Haleem!
•
•
PROCESS:
👉Take a bowl and add 1c Toor Dal, 1c Urad Dal, 1c Chana Dal, 1c wheat, 1c Moong Dal, 1c oats, 1c rice, 1/2c almonds, 1/2c cashews.
👉Soak all together in water for 4-5hrs
👉Take a kadai and add this soaked Dals and let it it cook on medium flame until it thickens
👉turn off the flame and let it cool
👉Take a mixer jar and blend it 
👉Now let’s cook mutton, Take bowl and 3-4lbs add mutton 
👉Add 1tbs red chili powder, 1tbs coriander powder, 1tbs black pepper powder, 1tbs salt, 5-6 cardamom seeds, 2-3 cinnamon sticks, 1tbs black cumin seeds, 1tbs cumin seeds, 4-5 black pepper, 5-6 cloves, squeeze half a lemon and give it a nice mix

👉Turn on the instant pot and add 3tbs oil
👉Add marinated mutton and pressure cook it for 30mins (if you use pressure cooker, cook it for 8-9whistles) 
👉Take out 2c of the gravy and set it a side
👉Mash the pieces by adding 1/2c fried onions and 2tbs ghee
👉Take a kadai and Add the paste that we blended earlier 
👉Now add mashed mutton and stir it continuously for 15mins on medium flame 
👉Add 1c of gravy and stir for another 15mins
👉Finally take a bowl and serve 
👉Don’t forget to top with fried onions, gravy and ghee

•

PROCESS:
👉Take a bowl and add 2 eggs
👉Add 1/2tbs salt, 1tbs black pepper, 1tbs red chili flakes, 1/4c milk and beat well 
👉set this a side
👉Now, take a pan and add 2tbs olive oil, 1/4c chopped green chilies, 1/2c chopped onions, 1/2c chopped spinach, 1/2tbs salt and fry for 4-5 mins
(Optional- you can add some other veggies like Bell peppers/ mushrooms)
👉Add egg mixture and let it cook for a min with the lid closed
👉Now, place a Roti/ chapati/ any flat bread on it and flip it over once the down side egg mixture is cooked 
👉let it cook on the other side and turn off the flame
👉finally serve it on a plate, cut into four pieces and enjoy!

Homemade Veg Salad 🥗 
•
•
PROCESS:
👉Soak combination of 2c black eyed peas + Fava beans for 5-6 hrs in water 
👉Drain the water and pressure cook for one whistle 
👉Take a bowl and Add cooked beans, 1/2c chopped Persian cucumber, 1/2c chopped carrots, 1/2c yellow bell peppers, 1/2c orange bell peppers, 1/2c cherry tomatoes, 1c chopped lettuce, 1c spring mix.
👉Add 1/2tbs salt, 1tbs black pepper powder, 1tbs red chili flakes, 2tbs lemon vinaigrette, 2tbs yogurt/ curd, 1/2c grilled asparagus, 2tbs olive oil and give it a nice mix
👉freeze it for like 10mins( optional )
👉finally enjoy the salad 
•
•
Tip: you can replace the beans with grilled paneer / grilled chicken
